other_tests.findings: Sinus rhythm at 87 bpm, left ventricular hypertrophy (LVH) with nonspecific ST changes.

Normal liver echogenicity, no intrahepatic biliary duct dilatation, patent portal vein with hepatopetal flow, normal gallbladder with gallstones, common bile duct measures 5 mm, 2 small liver cysts (9 mm and 8 mm), unremarkable right kidney, homogeneous spleen measuring 12 cm, unremarkable pancreas, no peripancreatic fluid collections.
